# Image archives — too heavy for git; reproduce via download scripts
assets
assets/
# Web-ready derivatives built by `pnpm shrink` from assets/
assets-web
assets-web/
# Poly Haven PBR textures — too heavy for git; reproduce via `pnpm textures`
public/textures/

# Regeneratable Wikimedia API response cache
metadata/.cache/

# Dependencies
node_modules
node_modules/
.pnpm-store/

# Claude Code local scratch
.claude/

# Build artifacts
dist/
build/
out/
.next/
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# Generated gallery data is committed so Docker/CI builds do not need the
# heavy local assets archive. Regenerate intentionally with `pnpm build:data`.

# react-email dev server scratch dir
.react-email/

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/settings.json
.idea/

# Logs / env
# `.env.production` is dotenvx-encrypted (the file's content is `KEY="encrypted:..."`)
# and SAFE to commit — the encryption is the whole point. Only the *.keys
# file (which holds the private key) must stay out of git.
*.log
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local
.env.keys

# Lockfile cruft (keep package-lock.json / pnpm-lock.yaml)
yarn.lock
# claude code
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/worktrees/

# standard defaults (mirrors ~/.config/git/ignore)
.DS_Store
._*
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/launch.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/settings.json
.idea/
.cursor/
*.swp
*~
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/
*.log

# env files (mirrors ~/.config/git/ignore — defense in depth)
# Note: dotenvx-encrypted env files (.env.production etc.) are intentionally
# allowed; only the unencrypted ones + the *.keys file are kept out.
.env
.env.local
.envrc.local
.env.keys
.vercel/
